  "text": "An important design feature for any descriptor-based retrieval system is that the distance metric in feature space correlates with perceptual similarity. To gauge this perceptual similarity, ground-truth information from user studies is needed. Interestingly, Forsyth [CITATION_1] criticizes the design of many existing image retrieval systems for not meeting real users' needs when they are based on image collections that are comprehensively tagged but are typically unrealistically small.",
